Neuroscience course is oriented for both Ph.D. and master degree students. Theoretical course provides the overview about the general and conceptual approaches in neuroscience. The following topics are covered during the course: bioelectrical processes in the nervous system, signal transduction, sensory systems, motor systems, and the integrative functions of central nervous system. Aim of practical courses is to study the selected research methods applied in the behavioural neuroscience.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Main aim of current course is to give the overview for master degree students in biomedicine about the conceptual and methodological approaches in neurosciences applied for study of brain function and behaviour.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completion of current course the student is able to present the main conceptual approaches in neurosciences. Also the students have the understanding about the relevant methods for study of brain functions and behaviour.
